        "FIGREF0": {
            "text": "10 which are identified by Choi et al to have higher DCD utilization are noted to all have increased number of patients on the waiting list post-DSA change, along with higher number of overall transplants. The long term effects may be different if financial constraints become more prominent.As I write this commentary, the world is struggling with the ravages of COVID-19 viral pandemic. All transplant activity has significantly slowed down if not come to a screeching halt in disease epicenters. In order to help sustain essential transplant activity, all major transplant organizations have recommended local procurement in order to decrease long distance travel to donor hospitals, especially across state borders. In this situation, acceptance of DCD donors could very well decrease ever more given the addition of an extra layer of uncertainty and/or lack of a suitable local procurement team.",
